#
# amsplot; python script; J. Alcaraz 09-Dec-2003
#
SCRIPT amsplot: 
		amsplot [options] [variable] [files]
	 to plot one AMS variable from a set of root files

	a) It checks the validity of [variable] and the existence of [files]
	b) It creates the file "amsplot.C"
	c) It executes "root amsplot.C" at the end (use "--test" to avoid this)
USAGES: 
	amsplot [variable] [root_file1] [root_file2] ...
	amsplot --list [variable] [file_with_list_of_root_files]
	amsplot --test [variable] [root_file1] [root_file2] ...
	amsplot --test --list [variable] [file_with_list_of_root_files]
EXAMPLES: 
	amsplot nTrTrack proton_1.root               --> #tracks in event
	amsplot nTrTrack proton_1.root proton_2.root --> #tracks in event
	amsplot nTrTrack proton*.root                --> #tracks in event
	amsplot '1<=nTrTrack<=5' gammas_*_*.root     --> #tracks in a range
	amsplot Header.Run helium.root.*             --> Run number
	amsplot Run helium.root.*                    --> Run number
	amsplot TrTrack.Rigidity ntp/*.root.*        --> Track rigidities
	amsplot 'TrTrack.Rigidity>0' my_file.root    --> Track rigidities>0
	amsplot 'TrTrack.NTrRecHit()' my_file.root   --> #hits on tracks
	amsplot 'TrTrack.HPhi[1]' my_file.root       --> Phi of first half-track
	amsplot 'TrTrack.HPhi[1]!=0' my_file.root    --> (HPhi==0 => not filled)
	amsplot 'TrTrack.iTrRecHit(2)' my_file.root  --> link to 2nd hit on track
	amsplot --test nParticle my_file.root        --> #particles; test mode
	amsplot --list nParticle list_of_root_files  --> #particles; list mode
IMPORTANT: 
	Please set the $AMSDir environment variable before using the script
